  "Notes": [
    {
      "Text": "Recommended update for grub2",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "Summary"
    },
    {
      "Text": "This update for grub2 fixes the following issues:\n\n- CVE-2024-56738: Fixed side-channel attack due to not \n  constant-time algorithm in grub_crypto_memcmp (bsc#1234959)\n\nOther fixes:\n- Fix test -f and -s do not work properly over the network files \n  served via tftp and http (bsc#1246157, bsc#1246237)\n- Skip mount point in grub_find_device function (bsc#1246231)\n\n",
      "Title": "Details",
      "Type": "General"
    },
